icular coloration; 15, female larva of penultimate instar with light cuticle and well-visible hypodermal coloration; 16, exuviae of fore leg with prothoracic pleurite; 17, exuviae of middle leg; 18, exuviae of hind leg with metathoracic pleurite and part of metanotum (arrow shows vestige of hind protopteron); 19, exuviae of abdomen; 20, exuviae of right half of pronotum and mesonotum; 21, head; 22, portion of cercus and paracercus in middle part; 23, apices of cercus and paracercus." captionText-3="FIGURES 24–27. Larvae of Potamocloeon edentatum sp. n. 24, maxilla (ventral view); 25, left half of labrum (dorsal view); 26–27, apices of left and right mandibles before molt to next larval instar. Abbreviations: ds1–ds3, dentisetae." captionText-4="FIGURES 28–36. Larvae of Potamocloeon edentatum sp. n. 28, 29, tergalii of 1st pair; 30–35, tergalii of 2nd–7th pairs; 36, labium (at left ventral view and musculature, at right dorsal view)." captionText-5="FIGURES 37–44. Larvae of Potamocloeon edentatum sp. n. 37, fore leg (dorsal view); 38, articulation of femur and tibia of middle leg (dorsal view); 39, fragment of fore tarsus (ventral view); 40, fragment of middle tarsus (ventral view); 41–42, claws; 43, exuviae of paraprocts and protogonostyli of male larva; 44, exuviae of 9th and 10th terga." captionText-6="FIGURES 45–51. Larval legs of Potamocloeon edentatum sp. n. (instead of long hairs, only their bases are shown as small rings). 45, fore femur (dorsal view); 46, middle femur (dorsal view); 47, fore tibia (anterior view); 48, middle tibia (anterior view); 49, hind tibia (anterior view); 50, fore tarsus (dorsal view), 51, middle tarsus (dorsal view)." captionText-7="FIGURES 52–55. Larval abdominal sterna of Potamocloeon edentatum sp. n. 52, halves of abdominal sterna II–VIII; 53, frag- ment of sternum III; 54, fragment of sternum V; 55, fragment of sternum VII." captionText-8="FIGURES 56–62. Potamocloeon edentatum sp. n. 56, abdominal terga of male imago; 57–59, male imagines; 60, abdominal sterna of male imago; 61–62, female imago (56, 60, holotype)." captionText-9="FIGURES 63–69. Potamocloeon edentatum sp. n. 63, subimaginal exuviae of tibia and tarsus of female fore leg; 64, the same, hind leg; 65, its imaginal hind leg; 66, subimaginal exuviae of mesopleuron; 67, subimaginal exuviae of left half of mesonotum; 68–69, genitals of male imagines (66–68, holotype)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3354879/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3354881/files/figure.png" httpUri-10="https://zenodo.org/record/3354899/files/figure.png" httpUri-11="https://zenodo.org/record/3354901/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3354883/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/3354885/files/figure.png" httpUri-4="https://zenodo.org/record/3354887/files/figure.png" httpUri-5="https://zenodo.org/record/3354889/files/figure.png" httpUri-6="https://zenodo.org/record/3354891/files/figure.png" httpUri-7="https://zenodo.org/record/3354893/files/figure.png" httpUri-8="https://zenodo.org/record/3354895/files/figure.png" httpUri-9="https://zenodo.org/record/3354897/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="300">Figs 1–76</figureCitation>
